The paper discusses testing of supervised classifiers using metamorphic testing, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of supervised classifiers also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application domains mentioned, such as computational biology and healthcare, suggest a connection to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the study evaluates the fault detection effectiveness of the MRs, which suggests a connection to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
